ne produces unique harmonics and overtones.' });\n   156→\n   157→    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=zylophone');\n   158→    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   159→    expect(res.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n   160→    expect(res.body.results[0].title).toBe('Zylophone Dynamics');\n   161→  });\n   162→\n   163→  // 17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n   164→  it('FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search', async () => {\n   165→    // Create a note\n   166→    const createRes = await request(appCtx.app)\n   167→      .post('/notes')\n   168→      .send({ title: 'Original Title', body: 'Original content about elephants.' });\n   169→    const noteId = createRes.body.note.id;\n   170→\n   171→    // Update it with unique content\n   172→    await request(appCtx.app)\n   173→      .put(`/notes/${noteId}`)\n   174→      .send({ title: 'Updated Title', body: 'Updated content about xylographics.' });\n   175→\n   176→    // Search for the new content\n   177→    const searchNew = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=xylographics');\n   178→    expect(searchNew.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n   179→\n   180→    // Search for the old content - should not find it\n   181→    const searchOld = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=elephants');\n   182→    expect(searchOld.body.results.length).toBe(0);\n   183→  });\n   184→\n   185→  // 18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n   186→  it('FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search', async () => {\n   187→    // Create a note with unique content\n   188→    const createRes = await request(appCtx.app)\n   189→      .post('/notes')\n   190→      .send({ title: 'Temporary Note', body: 'Quizzaciously unique content for deletion test.' });\n   191→    const noteId = createRes.body.note.id;\n   192→\n   193→    // Verify it appears in search\n   194→    let searchRes = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=quizzaciously');\n   195→    expect(searchRes.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n   196→\n   197→    // Delete it\n   198→    await request(appCtx.app).delete(`/notes/${noteId}`);\n   199→\n   200→    // Verify it no longer appears in search\n   201→    searchRes = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=quizzaciously');\n   202→    expect(searchRes.body.results.length).toBe(0);\n   203→  });\n   204→\n   205→  // 19. Special characters in query don't crash\n   206→  it(\"Special characters in query don't crash\", async () => {\n   207→    const specialQueries = [\n   208→      '/notes/search?q=hello%20world',\n   209→      '/notes/search?q=test%26test',\n   210→      '/notes/search?q=it%27s',\n   211→      '/notes/search?q=%3Cscript%3E',\n   212→      '/notes/search?q=foo%2Bbar',\n   213→      '/notes/search?q=a%2Fb',\n   214→    ];\n   215→\n   216→    for (const url of specialQueries) {\n   217→      const res = await request(appCtx.app).get(url);\n   218→      // Should return 200 (search endpoint exists and handles special chars gracefully)\n   219→      expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   220→      expect(Array.isArray(res.body.results)).toBe(true);\n   221→    }\n   222→  });\n   223→\n   224→  // 20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n   225→  it('Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset', async () => {\n   226→    const start = performance.now();\n   227→    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=programming');\n   228→    const elapsed = performance.now() - start;\n   229→\n   230→    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   231→    expect(elapsed).toBeLessThan(100);\n   232→  });\n   233→});\n   234→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AnngMM1D43pXHMLgqWXTtU","session_id":"4a04920e-671d-4890-9a70-f8a5a0e4e6c3","uuid":"f70e1c6e-1406-48cb-a260-fd44c85a4f63"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AnngMM1D43pXHMLgqWXTtU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully explored and read all the files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Codebase Overview\n\nThis is a **full-text search benchmark application** built with TypeScript, Express, and SQLite using better-sqlite3. The project implements a notes application with complete CRUD operations and full-text search capabilities.\n\n### File Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts (database setup and seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts (Express route handlers)\n│   ├── errors.ts (custom error classes)\n│   ├── server.ts (app factory)\n│   └── seed.ts (database seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts (CRUD tests)\n│   └── search.test.ts (search functionality tests)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n---\n\n## Detailed File Contents\n\n### 1. **package.json** (Full Contents)\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Scripts:**\n- `build`: Compile TypeScript\n- `lint`: Run ESLint\n- `test`: Run Vitest tests\n- `seed`: Seed database with sample notes\n\n---\n\n### 2. **src/db.ts** (Full Contents)\nDatabase initialization and seeding module:\n- **`createDatabase(path?)`**: Creates/opens a SQLite database with WAL mode and foreign key constraints enabled\n- **`seedDatabase(db)`**: Populates database with 40+ sample notes across various categories\n- **`getSeedNotes()`**: Returns array of sample notes with titles, bodies, and JSON tags\n\nContains 40 seed notes covering topics like:\n- Programming (TypeScript, Python, Rust, React, Docker, Kubernetes, GraphQL)\n- Cooking/Recipes (pasta, cookies, sourdough, risotto, thai food)\n- Travel (Tokyo, Paris, Appalachian Trail, Southeast Asia, Kilimanjaro)\n- Science (quantum computing, solar system, neural networks)\n- Music (jazz, guitar, classical)\n- Health/Fitness (yoga, meditation, Mediterranean diet)\n- And many more...\n\n---\n\n### 3. **src/models.ts** (Full Contents)\nTypeScript interfaces for type safety:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/routes.ts** (Full Contents)\nExpress route handlers implementing CRUD operations:\n\n**Routes:**\n- `GET /notes` - List all notes (with optional `?tag=X` filter)\n- `GET /notes/:id` - Get single note by ID\n- `POST /notes` - Create new note\n- `PUT /notes/:id` - Update note\n- `DELETE /notes/:id` - Delete note\n\n**Features:**\n- Tag filtering using `json_each()` for JSON array queries\n- Validation for required fields (title, body)\n- Timestamps (created_at, updated_at) automatically set\n- Proper HTTP status codes (201 for create, 204 for delete)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/errors.ts** (Full Contents)\nCustom error handling:\n\n```typescript\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(err, _req, res, _next) {\n  // Handles NotFoundError, ValidationError, and generic 500 errors\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **src/server.ts** (Full Contents)\nExpress app factory:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App\n```\n\n- Creates Express app with JSON middleware\n- Sets up routes and error handling\n- Auto-starts server on port 3000 (or `process.env.PORT`) if run directly\n\n---\n\n### 7. **src/seed.ts** (Full Contents)\nCLI script to seed a database file:\n\n```typescript\nconst dbPath = process.argv[2] || 'notes.db';\n// Creates database, seeds 40+ notes, logs count, closes\n```\n\nRun with: `npm run seed` or `npm run seed /path/to/db.db`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **tests/notes.test.ts** (Full Contents - 15 Test Cases)\n\nCRUD operation tests using Vitest + Supertest:\n\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\n---\n\n### 9. **tests/search.test.ts** (Full Contents - 20 Test Cases)\n\nFull-text search endpoint tests (requires search implementation):\n\n**Core Search Tests (1-7):**\n- Full-text search with `GET /notes/search?q=keyword`\n- Snippet results with `<mark>` tags highlighting matches\n- Relevance ranking (lower rank = more relevant)\n- Exact phrase matching with quoted queries\n- Returns fields: id, title, snippet, rank\n- Handles non-existent searches (empty results)\n- Returns 400 without or with empty `q` parameter\n\n**Pagination Tests (10-12):**\n- `page=1` returns first 20 results (max 20 per page)\n- `page=2` returns next batch\n- Response includes `total`, `page`, `perPage` fields\n\n**Autocomplete/Suggest Tests (13-15):**\n- `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix` returns up to 5 title suggestions\n- Matches prefix in titles (case-insensitive)\n- Returns 400 with empty query\n\n**Sync Tests (16-18):**\n- New notes appear in search immediately after creation\n- Updated notes have new content searchable, old content not searchable\n- Deleted notes disappear from search\n\n**Robustness Tests (19-20):**\n- Special characters in queries don't crash (various encoded chars)\n- Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **benchmark application** for full-text search in SQLite. The codebase is well-structured with:\n\n- **Database Layer**: SQLite with 40+ seed notes\n- **API Layer**: Express with CRUD endpoints for notes and tag filtering\n- **Search Layer**: (Tests indicate) FTS5 implementation expected with snippet generation, ranking, pagination, and autocomplete\n- **Testing**: Comprehensive 35 test cases covering all functionality\n- **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript with interfaces for data models\n\nThe project appears to be testing SQLite's FTS5 (Full-Text Search 5) capabilities for fast, indexed search on note content."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a327b70 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 30072\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 23104</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a04920e-671d-4890-9a70-f8a5a0e4e6c3","uuid":"d57c3a99-97c0-4734-aa8